data.current_description: Starts asynchronous cancellation on a long-running operation. The server makes a best effort to cancel the operation, but success is not guaranteed. If the server doesn't support this method, it returns `google.rpc.Code.UNIMPLEMENTED`. Clients can use Operations.GetOperation or other methods to check whether the cancellation succeeded or whether the operation completed despite cancellation. On successful cancellation, the operation is not deleted; instead, it becomes an operation with an Operation.error value with a google.rpc.Status.code of `1`, corresponding to `Code.CANCELLED`.
data.description_suggestion: Requests asynchronous cancellation of a long-running Cloud Shell operation. The server attempts to cancel the operation but success is not guaranteed. Returns an empty response immediately; use GetOperation to poll the operation status and determine if cancellation succeeded. On successful cancellation, the operation's status will be marked with error code CANCELLED. If the server does not support cancellation, returns UNIMPLEMENTED error.

message: Operation 'cloudshell.operations.cancel' has semantic quality issues: vague_summary, missing_context. Missing summary entirely. Description is overly verbose and uses technical jargon that could confuse AI agents about the actual behavior. Added clear summary and streamlined description to focus on key points: best-effort nature, how to check status, and expected outcomes. Simplified technical details while maintaining accuracy.

data.current_description: Starts asynchronous cancellation on a long-running operation. The server makes a best effort to cancel the operation, but success is not guaranteed. If the server doesn't support this method, it returns `google.rpc.Code.UNIMPLEMENTED`. Clients can use Operations.GetOperation or other methods to check whether the cancellation succeeded or whether the operation completed despite cancellation. On successful cancellation, the operation is not deleted; instead, it becomes an operation with an Operation.error value with a google.rpc.Status.code of `1`, corresponding to `Code.CANCELLED`.
data.description_suggestion: Requests asynchronous cancellation of a long-running Cloud Shell operation. Cancellation is best-effort and not guaranteed to succeed. After calling this operation, use GetOperation to check the cancellation status. On successful cancellation, the operation's status will be set to CANCELLED with an error code of 1. If the operation completes before cancellation takes effect, the operation will reflect its completed state. Returns an empty response. Returns UNIMPLEMENTED if the server does not support this method.
data.reasoning: Missing summary entirely. Description is overly verbose and uses technical jargon that could confuse AI agents about the actual behavior. Added clear summary and streamlined description to focus on key points: best-effort nature, how to check status, and expected outcomes. Simplified technical details while maintaining accuracy.
